headline: Comcast Stock Rises After Earnings. Why the Focus Is All on This Number.
summary: Comcast  stock was rising on Thursday after the cable and entertainment company topped Wall Street’s earnings targets and said it had lost fewer broadband subscribers than expected over the second quarter.  Shares in the NBCUniversal parent climbed 4.6% to $34 ahead of the opening bell.  Comcast reported adjusted earnings of $1.25 a share, as revenue climbed 2.1% from a year ago to $30.3 billion.
